FAQs

How do I know which skin treatment is right for me?

Every skin is unique, and the best treatment depends on your skin type, condition, and individual goals. At MG Clinic, Dr. Rohal conducts a thorough consultation—examining your skin, reviewing your medical history, and understanding your concerns. Based on this, a personalized treatment plan is created to ensure safe, effective, and natural-looking results.

 Are treatments safe for sensitive or darker skin?

Yes. At MG Clinic, we use advanced, FDA-approved technologies and tailor each treatment to suit your skin type and sensitivity level. Dr. Rohal has extensive experience in treating Indian and pigmented skin safely, minimizing risks like pigmentation or irritation, especially with procedures like laser, peels, and acne therapy.

 How many sessions will I need?

The number of sessions depends on the condition being treated. For example, acne or pigmentation treatments may show results in 3–4 sessions, while laser hair reduction typically requires 6–8 sessions. During your consultation, we’ll provide a realistic timeline and expected progress to keep your goals on track.

 Is there any downtime?

Some treatments like peels, lasers, or microneedling may cause temporary redness, dryness, or mild flaking—usually lasting 1–3 days. However, most procedures at MG Clinic are non-invasive with minimal downtime. Dr. Rohal also provides detailed aftercare instructions to ensure a smooth, comfortable recovery.
